content:
This module provides utilities for interacting with the GitHub App API, allowing the application to authenticate and manage its installations.

## Key Exports

*   **`getInstallationToken(installationId: number): Promise<string>`**
    Fetches a JSON Web Token (JWT) for a specific GitHub App installation. This token is used to authenticate API requests on behalf of the installation.

*   **`getInstallationLogin(installationId: number): Promise<string | null>`**
    Retrieves the login (username or organization name) associated with a given GitHub App installation ID. Returns `null` if the installation or account login cannot be found or if the request fails.

*   **`deleteInstallation(installationId: number): Promise<void>`**
    Deletes a specific GitHub App installation. This action revokes the app's access to the associated repository or organization.

## Usage Example

```typescript
import { getInstallationToken, getInstallationLogin, deleteInstallation } from './lib/github-app';

async function manageGitHubApp(installationId: number) {
  try {
    // Get a token for the installation
    const token = await getInstallationToken(installationId);
    console.log('Installation Token:', token);

    // Get the login of the installation owner
    const login = await getInstallationLogin(installationId);
    console.log('Installation Login:', login);

    // Example of deleting an installation (use with caution)
    // await deleteInstallation(installationId);
    // console.log(`Installation ${installationId} deleted.`);

  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error managing GitHub App:', error);
  }
}

// Example usage with a hypothetical installation ID
// manageGitHubApp(12345678);
```

## Authentication

This module relies on environment variables for GitHub App authentication:

*   `GITHUB_APP_ID`: The ID of your GitHub App.
*   `GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY`: The private key for your GitHub App, including necessary newline characters (which are handled by the `replace(/\n/g, "\n")` logic).
